            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "For `:h LspProgress`: If you want to be fully correct, the `nvim_echo` should set the `id` to\r\n```lua\r\n          id = 'lsp.' .. pev.data.params.token,\r\n```\r\nthe [ProgressToken](https://microsoft.github.io/language-server-protocol/specifications/lsp/3.17/specification/#progress) the progress is reported for -- in case there's multiple progress notifications, like for luals. If you want to be robust for multiple servers attached to the same buffer, you'd probably want to combine the two?\r\n\r\n(Feel free to ignore if that's too involved.)",
            "created_at": "2026-04-01T09:19:11Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38584#issuecomment-4168714406",
